<item>
            <title>[LU-17960] LAST_ID mismatch improvement</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17960</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Normally if LAST_ID known by MDT and OST shouldn&apos;t differ too much, and if the one in lov_objid (on MDT) is OST_MAX_PRECREATE (20000) behind the LAST_ID on OST, it&apos;s not handled currently because it&apos;s hard to tell which one is corrupt.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can be improved in two aspects:&lt;br/&gt;
1. &quot;lfsck -t layout&quot; should update LAST_ID with the known max ID. (it&apos;s not updated if it&apos;s not less than the known max ID), so after lfsck this LAST_ID is correct.&lt;br/&gt;
2. once lfsck has finished check, trust the LAST_ID on OST, and reply it to MDT on precreate, and MDT will use it instead of its own.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="82971">LU-17960</key>
            <summary>LAST_ID mismatch improvement</summary>
