                            <comment id="419320" author="laisiyao" created="Fri, 28 Jun 2024 13:05:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually the last created FID on OSP is from OST, and only in deleting orphans phase in the first precreate, it will use the last used FID in &apos;lovobj_id&apos;. So this improvement is actually for the deleting orphan phase, and for the mismatch issue found on customer site, we can always trust the last created FID on OST, because it&apos;s maintained in memory, not just read from disk (which happens in deleting phase). I&apos;ll file another ticket for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
